Abigail Spanberger Photographer: Win McNamee/Getty Images Photographer: Win McNamee/Getty Images Democratic Representative Abigail Spanberger won re-election to the Virginia seat she flipped in 2018, defeating Republican state delegate Nick Freitas, the Associated Press projected. Spanberger, a former CIA operative, is a member of the fiscally conservative Blue Dog Coalition. The district, which includes Richmond suburbs, was won by President Donald Trump in 2016.